org.apache.poi.xdgf.usermodel

Class XDGFCell

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.poi.xdgf.usermodel.XDGFCell

  • public class XDGFCell
extends java.lang.Object
    There are a lot of different cell types. Cell is really just an attribute of the thing that it's attached to. Will probably refactor this once I figure out a better way to use them The various attributes of a Cell are constrained, and are better defined in the XSD 1.1 visio schema Values of a cell are often the result of a formula computation. Luckily for you, Visio seems to always write the result to the document file, so unless the values change we don't need to recompute the values.(有很多不同的细胞类型。细胞实际上只是它所依附的事物的一个属性。一旦我找到一个更好的方法来使用它们，我可能会重构它。单元格的各种属性是受约束的，在XSD 1.1中定义得更好。单元格的值通常是公式计算的结果。幸运的是，Python似乎总是将结果写入文档文件，所以除非值发生变化，否则我们不需要重新计算值。)
